Infrastructure:
- 2 HAProxy Load Balancers (clustered)
- 1 Web Server (Nginx)
- 1 Application Server
- 1 Database Server (MySQL)
- 1 additional server added to split components

Purpose of Elements:
- Second Load Balancer: Prevents SPOF, enables high availability
- Web Server: Serves static content, proxies dynamic requests
- Application Server: Processes backend logic
- Database Server: Stores persistent data
- New Server: Enables separation of roles and better scalability

Application Server vs Web Server:
- Web Server handles static files and proxies requests
- Application Server executes dynamic logic and interacts with database
